    <note>Zhan(1) Dafang [168] Liangchen's [3117] sons and grandsons received offices when he was executed by the rebel Fang(1) La [3298]. Dafang was Jingzhi's [7146] father. Another son, Huizhi [3116], served as Tiju Fujian shibo between 1195 and 1200, Liangzhe yunpan in 1205-6 and was appointed Junqi jian in 1206. Huizhi's heir was his elder brother Jingzhi's [7146] son, Biaomin [3118]. Huizhi was Zeng(1) Ji's [1692] grandson-in-law. Fujian TZ, 32.17b, 124.24a; XNYL, 153.3a, 156.15a, 157.8b, 158.3a, 8a; Xianchun Linan zhi, 50.9b; Lu You, WJ, 39.6b. CBD, 4, 3276.</note>
